## UX Rationale

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| Order Panel always visible on right | No toggle — instant table selection shows order |
| Table Grid always visible on left | Quick table switching without losing context |
| Menu stays open after adding item | Add multiple items fast without reopening |
| Cash is default payment method | Most common in Thai restaurants |
| Amount pre-filled to total | Cashier only adjusts for exact change |
| Close Table + Print Receipt one button | Common end-of-meal workflow |
| Keyboard shortcuts for everything | Power users don't need mouse |
| 44px+ touch targets | POS runs on tablets with finger input |
| Skeleton loading (not spinners) | Shows structure, feels faster |
| Inline quantity controls | Faster than opening a detail dialog |